				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>From The Oxford English Dictionary Word of the Day:</p>
<blockquote><p><strong>first foot, n.</strong></p>
<p>. . . .<br />
1.</span> <em title="English regional">Eng. regional</em> (<em title="northern">north.</em>), <em title="Scottish">Sc.</em>, and <em>Irish English</em> (<em title="northern">north.</em>) The first person to cross a householder&#8217;s threshold in the New Year.<br />
. . . .</p>
<p>1883   <span class="smallCaps">J. Parker</span> <em>Tyne Chylde</em> 4</span>   How glad..the dear soul was when she had a good ‘first-foot’ on New Year&#8217;s morning.</p></blockquote>
